9 Dekalb Avenue, at the N. E. corner of Albee Square, showing, under construction, the Dime Savings Bank of Brooklyn. The William Kennedy Construction Company are the builders.

April 7, 1932

P. L. Sperr

(2)

The bank, when completed. The colonnade is in the Ionic order of classical Greek architecture.

April 27, 1940

P. L. Sperr
